  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with cooking spray.",
    "Pat dry chicken wings with paper towels and place on the baking sheet.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together paprika, cumin, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Brush olive oil over the chicken wings, then sprinkle the spice mixture evenly.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes.",
    "Increase oven temperature to broil. Broil for an additional 5-7 minutes, until crispy.",
    "Remove from oven and brush with lemon juice.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
